olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet diced bacon
1 packet Slivered Almonds
2 tomato
1 packet basil pesto
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

Boil the kettle. Cut the potato into bite-sized chunks. Place the potato in a
large saucepan, cover with boiling water and simmer over a high heat until
easily pierced with a knife, 10-12 minutes. Drain the potato and return to the
saucepan. Toss with the chicken-style stock powder and set aside to cool.

While the potato is cooking, heat a medium frying pan with a drizzle of olive
oil over a medium-high heat. Cook the diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon
until just turning golden, 3-4 minutes. Add the slivered almonds and cook,
stirring, until golden, 1-2 minutes. Set aside to cool.

While the bacon is cooking, roughly chop the tomato. Add the bacon,
almonds and basil pesto to the potato. Toss to coat and season to taste.

Divide the bacon and pesto potato salad between two reusable containers
and set aside to cool. When the potato salad has cooled, top with the tomato,
spinach & rocket mix and grated Parmesan cheese. At lunchtime, toss the
salad to combine.

TIP: This potato salad is best enjoyed cooled!